        a                        fabio:Figure ;
        dc:description           "Figure 3. Aechmellina falcifera. (a) holotype, SMF 26280, early astogeny; Cretaceous, early Campanian, Goniotheutis quadrata Zone, White Chalk, Lägerdorf, Schleswig-Holstein, Germany. (b–d) NHMUK BZ 757; early Campanian, Sehnde-Höver, Lower Saxony, Germany; (b) autozooids and avicularia; (c) opesiae of two autozooids, that on the upper left fertile; (d) avicularium. Scale bars: a = 1 mm; b = 500 µm; c = 200 µm; d = 100 µm." ;
        fabio:hasRepresentation  "https://zenodo.org/record/4747147/files/figure.png" .

